  "body": "### Environment information\r\n\r\n* `brownie` Version: 1.17.2\r\n* OS: Pop!_OS (Light Theme)\r\n\r\n### What was wrong?\r\n\r\nThe font in the brownie console is not theme aware. That makes it unreadable or even invisible by default in light themes.\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed?\r\n\r\nA quick user fix is to change theme in `brownie-config.yaml`.\r\nFor example:\r\n```\r\nconsole:\r\n  color_style: manni\r\n```\r\nlist of themes: https://help.farbox.com/pygments.html\r\n\r\nBut the best way to solve this would be to have the console be theme-aware by default.",
